### [Matthew Chapter 21](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#001.md)

[Matthew 21:1](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">mat 21:1</span></span>

nigh unto Jerusalem

([Mat 21:1-9](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#001).md); ([Zac
9:9](../../../bib/kjv/zac009.htm#009).md); ([Zac
14:4-9](../../../bib/kjv/zac014.htm#004).md). The two advents are in
striking contrast.

[Matthew 21:4](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">mat 21:4</span></span>

fulfilled

The king's final and official offer of Himself according to ([Zac
9:9](../../../bib/kjv/zac009.htm#009).md). Acclaimed by an unthinking
multitude whose real belief is expressed in ([Mat
21:11](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#011).md); but with no welcome from the
official representatives of the nation, He was soon to hear the
multitude shout: "Crucify him."

[Matthew 21:12](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">mat 21:12</span></span>

cast

See ([Luk 19:45](../../../bib/kjv/luk019.htm#045).md); ([Mar
11:15-18](../../../bib/kjv/mar011.htm#015).md).

Compare ([Joh 2:13-25](../../../bib/kjv/joh002.htm#013).md) which
introduced, as this cleansing closed, the offer of Christ to Israel as
King.

[Matthew 21:17](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">mat 21:17</span></span>

Bethany

