[Matthew 21:44](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#044.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_044">mat 21:44</span></span>

stone shall be broken

Christ, as the "Stone", is revealed in a threefold way:

\(1\) To Israel Christ, coming not as a splendid monarch but in the form
of a servant, is a stumbling stone and rock of offence. ([Isa
8:14](../../../bib/kjv/isa008.htm#014).md); ([Isa
8:15](../../../bib/kjv/isa008.htm#015).md); ([Rom
9:32](../../../bib/kjv/rom009.htm#032).md); ([Rom
9:33](../../../bib/kjv/rom009.htm#033).md); ([Co1
1:23](../../../bib/kjv/co1001.htm#023).md); ([Pe1
2:8](../../../bib/kjv/pe1002.htm#008).md).

\(2\) to the church, Christ is the foundation stone and the head of the
corner ([Co1 3:11](../../../bib/kjv/co1003.htm#011).md); ([Eph
2:20-22](../../../bib/kjv/eph002.htm#020).md); ([Pe1
2:4](../../../bib/kjv/pe1002.htm#004).md); ([Pe1
2:5](../../../bib/kjv/pe1002.htm#005).md).

\(3\) to the Gentile world-powers

(see "Gentiles," ([Luk 21:24](../../../bib/kjv/luk021.htm#024).md); ([Rev
16:19](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#019).md)

He is to be the smiting-stone of destruction ([Dan
2:34](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#034).md). Israel stumbled over Christ;
the church is built upon Christ; Gentile world-dominion will be broken
by Christ.

See "Armageddon" ([Rev 16:14](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#014).md); ([Rev
19:19](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#019).md).

And whosoever

Or, Whosoever falls on this stone shall be crushed togetherthat is, the
Jews ([Isa 8:14](../../../bib/kjv/isa008.htm#014).md); ([Rom
9:32](../../../bib/kjv/rom009.htm#032).md); ([Rom
9:33](../../../bib/kjv/rom009.htm#033).md); ([Co1
1:23](../../../bib/kjv/co1001.htm#023).md)\] but on whomsoever it may fall,
he will be scattered as dust (Greek, "likmaō", "winnowed"), that is, the
Gentile nations. ([Dan 2:34](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#034).md); ([Dan
2:35](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#035).md); ([Dan
2:45](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#045).md).

(See Scofield) - ([Dan 2:35](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#035).md).

